      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but it feels like you're saying one side is just \"sensible\" and the other is just an obstacle to safety. if someone believes the Constitution is the supreme law and that the right to self-defense is fundamental to liberty, is that just a \"wrong\" opinion? why does the statistical argument automatically carry more weight than the legal/philosophical one in your view?",
